CHANGELOG.md:660:- Added depth-2 generation composer-hook end-to-end test coverage (frac-0077): `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py` now includes `GenerationComposerHookEndToEndTests`, which drives the public composer-hook surface (`_should_queue_now`, `build_generation_request`, `MIN_GENERATION_INTERVAL_SECONDS`, `MIN_DAILY_BUDGET_REMAINING_USD`) plus the duet-composer integration `_post_song_generation_hook` through the full gate -> build -> enqueue cycle. The end-to-end scenarios cover a happy-path enqueue with a real builder via a thin `_ConditionerAdapter` that asserts the queued payload equals `build_generation_request(...)`, idempotency key matches `request_hash`, and the request hash is a 64-char content-addressed digest; gate-denial paths for low daily budget at the `MIN_DAILY_BUDGET_REMAINING_USD` floor, sampler-dominating antipatterns, working-ambience low arc payoff, and rate-limited recent enqueue under `MIN_GENERATION_INTERVAL_SECONDS`, all confirming `_post_song_generation_hook` returns `None` with no queue traffic; deterministic-builder identity for equal inputs and distinct hashes/seeds for changed mode or arc phase; and a JSON-safe round-trip via `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)` on the built request and the queued payload. `tests/test_test_generation_composer_hook_depth.py` pins `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function composer-hook assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/composer_hook.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4514 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:670:- Added depth-2 functional-harmony end-to-end test coverage (frac-0072): `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` now includes `FunctionalHarmonyEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing harmony public API through live-like keyboard/garden/outdoor/inner inputs, resolved harmonic planning, reharm lookup, modulation continuity checks, score-tree section construction, and JSON-safe round-trip output. The end-to-end scenarios verify meaningful `HarmonicPlan` fields (`G:lydian` keyboard authority, extended palette, pedal-point voicing, scene keys, section functions/cadences/progressions, chord-degree triads, harmonic functions, transition intents, and modulation path), align `reharm_plan_for_song()` / `progression_bank_for_section()` with the resolved plan, assert tension and cadence targets across the arc, and prove `ScoreTree` persistence preserves derived harmonic function and transition intent metadata. `tests/test_test_functional_harmony_depth.py` pins `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function harmony assertions and production `reharmonizer.py`, `harmonic_planner.py`, and `score_tree.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4487 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:676:- Added depth-2 counterpoint_rules end-to-end test coverage (frac-0069): `tests/test_counterpoint_rules.py` now ships a `CounterpointRulesEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public counterpoint registry surface (`best_rule_for_phase`, `rules_for_phase`, `rules_for_leader_role`, `rules_for_follower_role`, `rules_for_voice_pair`, `resolve_rule`, `get_rule`, `motion_profile`, `analyze_dissonance`, `verify_resolution_sequence`, `resolution_completeness_score`, `weighted_voice_leading_smoothness`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, `counterpoint_pair_summary`) end-to-end through 11 scenario tests covering: per-phase best-rule resolution against the documented Divination/Emergence/Conversation/Convergence/Crystallization expectations with affinity bounded in [0, 1]; voice-pair query intersections and unknown-role empty-result handling; `resolve_rule` known/alias/unknown fallback chains plus registry fallback validity; mixed-sequence motion classification including single-note and mismatched-length safe defaults; contrary-motion `score_counterpoint_fit` / `rank_counterpoint_rules` agreement with `recommend_counterpoint_rule` and bounded sub-metrics; realistic melody/bass dissonance + resolution analysis with JSON-safe annotation payloads; `counterpoint_pair_summary` payload shape, key set, JSON round-trip, and consistency with the underlying `CounterpointFit`; registry coverage equality with `REQUIRED_RELATIONSHIPS` and `REQUIRED_PHASES`; mixed-dissonance resolution completeness and weighted-smoothness penalties; voice-pair-compatible-only ranking for melody/bass pairs; phase-sensitive summary differences with JSON round-trip; and parallel/static/oblique extreme motion-profile sequences. `tests/test_test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins `tests/test_counterpoint_rules.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestRegistryCompleteness`, `TestEntryFields`, `TestArcPhaseAffinity`, `TestVoicePairQueries`, `TestLookups`, `TestIntervalConstraints`, `TestImmutability`, `TestVerificationAndScoring`, and `TestDissonanceMetadata` assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4476 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:688:- Added depth-2 cast-planner end-to-end test coverage (frac-0063): `tests/test_cast_planner.py` now ships a `TestCastPlannerEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public cast-planner surface (`select_cast_ids`, `assemble_cast`, plus the exported `CORE_ROLES` / `SUPPORT_ROLES` / `SAMPLER_METADATA_KEY` constants) through table-driven and looped end-to-end paths. The new tests sweep cast-history/energy combinations to confirm the canonical melody/rhythm/harmony lead with at least one support role across multiple support-role winners; sweep `(voice_count_target, max_chars, expected_size)` cases to verify clamping to `max_chars` and core-role ordering at every size; sweep preferred-synth palettes (`sw_bowed/sw_choir`, `sw_sampler/sw_bell`, `sw_drone/sw_recorder`) to confirm matching characters are promoted into the cast at `voice_count_target=5`; simulate a four-round cast-history rotation that pushes the most-recent support pick out of the next cast; drive multi-piece `assemble_cast` runs to verify piece-derived sampler-selector kwargs (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`) propagate correctly and the sampler summary is mirrored in both the assembled entry's `sample_record` and the metadata mapping; round-trip the assembled diagnostic payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys; and sweep selector outcomes (`sample`, `None`, `sample`) to verify `sampler_voice` always lands in the cast while `sampler_sample` metadata is attached only when the selector returns a sample. `tests/test_cast_planner_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing `test_select_cast_*`, `test_voice_count_target_*`, `test_preferred_synths_*`, and `test_sampler_*` assertions are preserved unchanged; the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py` source remains unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4409 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:696:- Added depth-2 artist-identity end-to-end test coverage (frac-0059): `tests/test_artist_identity.py` now ships a `TestArtistIdentityEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public artist-identity surface (`select_mode`, `apply_mode_to_commission`, `next_tonal_choice`, `MODES`, `MODES_BY_NAME`, `HOME_TONAL_MAP`, `VOICE_ROLES`, `SIGNATURE_VOICES`) through looped, table-driven end-to-end methods. The new tests sweep every `ArtistMode` for required commission metadata keys, tempo-band membership across many seeds, voice-count propagation, silence/restraint/harmony field propagation, sampler-density propagation, voice/groove/modal CSV serialization, the `mode_avoid_attention_pullers` string contract, deterministic application across non-zero seeds, input-dict immutability, JSON round-trip safety, and preservation of pre-existing commission keys; verify the entire `HOME_TONAL_MAP` (only `B` is home, `D` and `F#` are the unique distance-1 neighbors, every distance is a non-negative int); walk the documented `select_mode` priority matrix including the inclusive 0.6 STORM threshold, screen-active gating that requires `presence='present'`, equivalent evening/night routing, and a full presence/time/severity/screen sweep that always returns a known mode; sweep `next_tonal_choice` across many seeds for every mode confirming roots stay in `HOME_TONAL_MAP` and scales stay in `mode.preferred_modes`, determinism per (mode, seed), and that modulation-willingness correlates with venturing (SOLITARY <= COMPANION <= STORM); and run the end-to-end `select -> apply -> choose` pipeline across a presence/time/screen matrix with JSON-safe payloads. `tests/test_artist_identity_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing artist-identity assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
