CHANGELOG.md:766:- Added depth-2 sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0023): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan` so diagnostics and composer callers can inspect a concrete `sw_sampler` dispatch before or after buffer loading. The plan reports sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and the canonical `/s_new` synth argument pairs; live `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` helper, preserving existing OSC ordering and lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins named density bands, loaded/unloaded plan output, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:780:- Added depth-2 lung capacity report helpers (frac-0016): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/lung_capacity.py` now exposes frozen `LaneBreathStat` and `LungCapacityReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_breath_stat`, `analyze_lung_capacity`, and `summarize_lung_capacity_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R11 rule once and read back per-lane breath outcomes (lane name, voice, role, resolved capacity seconds, inserted vs. tagged breath counts, and an `applies` flag for role-gated wind/voice lanes), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary (totals, lane counts, applied-lane count, per-lane entries) without re-walking the tracker scene tree. Existing `LungCapacityRule.apply`, `apply_lung_capacity`, and `lung_capacity_seconds_for_voice` semantics are preserved so MIDI/Theramini/score-tree callers and `tests/test_lung_capacity_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_lung_capacity_depth.py` pins inserted-vs-tagged counting, non-wind lane non-application, scene/song aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:784:- Added depth-2 production course helpers (frac-0014): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/production_course.py` now exposes frozen `CourseSummary`, `ChapterDigest`, `ArcPhaseSnapshot`, and `CourseArcPlan` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_course`, `chapter_digest`, `catalog_digest`, `arc_phase_snapshot`, `arc_phase_snapshots`, `course_titles`, `plan_course_arc`, and `validate_course` so runtime diagnostics and tests can render an operator-readable view of a section course (chapter count, transition type, mix role, resolved concept titles in declared chapter order), digest each chapter with its first three sample concept values, snapshot every required arc phase with a `sparse` / `balanced` / `dense` density bucket, plan an arc end-to-end by reusing `course_for_section` across a sequence of section descriptors with the last transition cleanly resolving to `terminal`, and report unknown-value chapters as a sorted tuple. Existing `REQUIRED_CHAPTER_IDS`, `REQUIRED_PHASE_NAMES`, `COURSE_CHAPTERS`, `ARC_PHASE_PROFILES`, `load_course_chapters`, `load_arc_phase_profiles`, `course_chapter`, `course_concept`, `arc_phase_profile`, `transition_type_for_section`, and `course_for_section` semantics are preserved so the score-tree composer and `tests/test_production_course_knowledge_base.py` / `tests/test_production_course_integration.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_production_course_depth.py` pins summary title order, chapter digest metadata + `KeyError` on unknown ids, catalog digest coverage, density bucketing + `KeyError` on unknown phase, end-to-end arc plan + empty short-circuit, and validator behavior, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:788:- Added depth-2 genre literacy helpers (frac-0012): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/genre_literacy.py` now exposes frozen `GenreSummary` / `GenreBlend` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_strategy`, `genre_compatibility`, `blend_genre_strategies`, and `recommend_genre_sequence` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can render a stable per-genre summary (label, tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, voice count, dominant grooves, top arc phases, calm/balanced/intense mood bucket), score a bounded `[0.0, 1.0]` symmetric compatibility between two traditions from arc-affinity cosine, modal/groove Jaccard ratios, and texture/chromatic distance, blend numeric hints with a clamped `[0.0, 1.0]` weight (tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, rubato tolerance, repetition tolerance, spatial width, sorted shared modal preferences), and plan one genre per supplied arc phase with rolling fatigue from prior selections. Existing `GenreStrategy`/`REQUIRED_GENRES` data, `strategy_for_genre`, `all_strategies`, `genre_arc_affinity`, `best_genres_for_phase`, and `select_genre` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_genre_literacy_depth.py` pins summary stability and mood bucketing, compatibility self-identity / symmetry / boundedness with related-vs-contrasted ranking, blend interpolation / clamp / modal intersection, sequence per-phase coverage with no immediate repeats, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:794:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:796:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins tracker→world→default fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
CHANGELOG.md:800:- Added depth-2 character registry helpers (frac-0006): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/character_registry.py` now exposes pure helpers `voice_of`, `mode_gain_for`, `params_for`, `summarize_registry`, `voices_by_role`, and `find_voices_by_synth` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can project voice metadata, resolve per-mode gain overrides, merge voice params with caller overrides (skipping `None`-valued overrides), and inspect the registry without reaching into raw mapping shapes. Malformed `voice` entries are ignored across the diagnostic helpers, gain overrides coerce through `float()` with default fallback on non-numeric values, and bucketed/match outputs are deterministically sorted. Existing `CharacterRegistry`, `VOICE_SAMPLER_*` constants, `SAMPLER_DEFAULT_PARAMS`, and `SAMPLER_MODE_GAIN_OVERRIDES` are preserved so `cast_planner`, `duet_composer`, and `tests/test_character_registry.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_character_registry_depth.py` pins voice projection, gain override resolution, params merge with `None`-skip, registry summary histograms, role-bucket sorting, synth-match filtering, and fractal depth ≥ 2.
CHANGELOG.md:804:- Added depth-2 narrative arc helpers (frac-0004): `my-claw/tools/inner_life/narrative_arc.py` now exposes pure helpers `phase_at`, `phase_progress`, `phase_profile`, and `arc_summary` for resolving the 30-minute build/rise/climax/resolve/rest cycle without mutating an `InnerState`, with clamped position lookup, per-phase progress fractions, and stable diagnostic labels (`gathering`, `rising`, `peaking`, `resolving`, `resting`, `unknown`). `complete_cycle` now aggregates `today_events` into an `event_type_counts` histogram (bucketing missing/blank `type` keys under `unknown`), counts opinions, and records `final_phase`/`final_position` alongside the existing cycle/duration/mood/mode keys. Existing `update_arc`, `start_new_cycle`, `energy_for_phase`, and `action_weight_for_phase` semantics are preserved so `decision_engine` and `inner_life.main` callers are unaffected; `tests/test_narrative_arc_depth.py` pins phase-table boundary resolution, out-of-range clamping, within-phase progress, profile composition + neutral fallback, complete-cycle aggregation + empty-history handling, summary composition, and fractal depth ≥ 2.
CHANGELOG.md:849:- Added the missing CCS-028 sample-usage journal seam for tracker pieces: `senseweave.usage_journal` now serializes the richer per-piece sampler fields (`started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used`, `transformations`, `clicks`) while preserving the legacy `timestamp` / `samples_played` aliases, `music_tracker_runtime.ScheduledTrackerEvent` now carries sample-gesture metadata through playback emission, `duet_composer.py` now records actual emitted sample-lane events into the post-piece journal hook, and new regression coverage in `tests/test_usage_journal.py`, `tests/test_music_tracker_runtime.py`, and `tests/test_usage_journal_integration.py` composes a short score-tree piece end to end and proves the written journal entry contains populated sample usage, transformations, and arc payoff data.
CHANGELOG.md:854:- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
CHANGELOG.md:855:- Added a piece-aware sampler cast-planning seam: `senseweave.cast_planner` now exposes `assemble_cast(...)`, which derives selector kwargs from a piece fixture (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`/`patch_name`), returns assembled cast entries, and mirrors any pre-selected sampler summary onto the sampler cast entry as `sample_record`; sampler summaries now also derive `duration_sec` from capture-shaped records via `frame_count / sample_rate`, and `duet_composer._get_cast()` now routes through the shared cast assembler. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_cast_planner.py` for fixture-piece planning and capture-shaped sample summaries, while keeping the targeted `cast_planner` + `sampler_dispatch` suites green.
CHANGELOG.md:859:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md` as the missing CCS-033 companion page: it states the sampler's aesthetic goals, names the three core usages (memory of place, self-quotation, curated found-sound library), explains `sw_sampler` as the quintet's memory voice, and defines the intended listener experience plus the five governing principles without duplicating implementation detail; added `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_artistic_intent.py` to pin the document's required sections, artistic concepts, concise length, and sampler-doc cross-links, and linked the new page from the sampler architecture doc and the musicianship roadmap.
CHANGELOG.md:860:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:861:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
CHANGELOG.md:863:- Closed the server-side gap on the new master-bus sampler controls: added a `master_smooth.scd` SuperCollider source stub for `sw_master_smooth` that declares `sampler_amp` and `sampler_bypass_comp` (both default 1.0) alongside the existing `amp` / `drive` / `warmth` / `reverb` / `room` surface; refactored `start_audio.sh` and `restart_composer.sh` to seed the master node via `senseweave.master_bus.master_bus_s_new_args()` so the boot-time `/s_new sw_master_smooth` arg list stays in lockstep with `DEFAULT_MASTER_BUS_VALUES`; added `tests/test_master_smooth_scd.py` to pin the stub's control declarations and the boot scripts' helper-driven seeding.
CHANGELOG.md:870:- Added executable production-course curriculum exercises: `ExerciseSpec` now carries a runnable `template` and explicit `expected_features` while preserving the legacy `expected` alias; generated exercise specs include both metadata forms; and the EMSD curriculum now has verifier-backed exercises for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full-arc production.
CHANGELOG.md:871:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
CHANGELOG.md:873:- Added dissonance/resolution metadata checks to counterpoint rules using music_theory.py interval consonance data: new `DissonanceAnnotation` and `DissonanceReport` dataclasses carry full `Interval` objects from the music theory library; `analyze_dissonance()` annotates each vertical interval in a voice-pair sequence with consonance classification and stepwise resolution status; `verify_resolution_sequence()` validates that all sharp dissonances resolve properly; `resolution_completeness_score()` returns a 0.0-1.0 ratio; and `weighted_voice_leading_smoothness()` penalizes unresolved dissonances in the smoothness metric.
CHANGELOG.md:877:- Added installation-aware acoustic ecology policies: new `acoustic_ecology.py` module provides `resolve_acoustic_ecology()` which translates presence, cadence, day phase, room activity, attention state, and dwell time into a frozen `AcousticEcologyPolicy` with hard ceilings for volume, onset density, and spectral brightness, silence window parameters, ordered source preferences, keynote privilege weights, and density/voice caps. Sleep and wind-down modes enforce non-negotiable ceilings that cannot be overridden by any modifier. Performance attention overrides wind-down constraints when the human is actively engaged. Room activity boosts keynote privilege so the room's own soundscape is the acoustic content.
CHANGELOG.md:881:- Implemented ST1-ST6 of the score-tree songwriting stack end to end: added `piece_commission.py`, `piece_brief.py`, `form_grammar.py`, `score_tree.py`, `recursive_composer.py`, `composition_gate.py`, `tracker_compiler.py`, and `piece_queue.py`; extended `repertoire_memory.py` to store structural score-tree summaries; and rewired `duet_composer.py` so tracker solo mode can commission a piece, build a complete score tree, gate it, compile it into tracker scenes, and precompose the next piece into a small persistent queue instead of treating the tracker as the composer.
CHANGELOG.md:890:- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
CHANGELOG.md:892:- Fixed recalled motif rhythm metadata so later sections that borrow earlier material inherit the current scene's rhythm/progression profile instead of leaking the source scene's old `rhythm_development`.
CHANGELOG.md:893:- Added arrangement automation curves to tracker playback: `music_tracker.py` now derives `arrangement_curve` from section rhythm, writes row-point automation for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, shapes note velocity across each lane's active window, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` / `duet_composer.py` now expose and apply interpolated automation to the live master bus during the section. Low density also thins optional color/counter runtime events while preserving melody and bass continuity.
CHANGELOG.md:896:- Fixed the live score-tree runtime on CypherClaw: `duet_composer.py` now derives commission context defensively from the world when `TrackerPlan` lacks `day_phase` / `weekly_phase`, `master_bus.py` now exposes an explicit `sw_master_smooth` seed helper, and `restart_composer.sh` now reseeds that master node again after the new composer PID is confirmed alive so the first piece does not run with scene-level `/n_set` traffic targeting a dead node.
CHANGELOG.md:897:- Added a concrete score-tree composition spec for the next songwriting pass: `cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md` now defines the piece commission layer, narrative brief contract, section-function grammar, score-tree data model, recursive composer, composition gate, tracker compiler, repertoire score-tree memory, and rollout phases needed to move CypherClaw from short tracker-first sketches toward longer, more varied composed pieces.
CHANGELOG.md:910:- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
CHANGELOG.md:911:- Added a replayable musical integration regression that exercises the composer-state -> sampler-plan -> sample-playback -> self-listener glyph state -> face-status chain, so this integration can be verified without a live host.
CHANGELOG.md:912:- Hardened the live audio runtime after the Scarlett/JACK outage: `start_audio.sh` now links the repo SynthDef bundle into `~/.local/share/SuperCollider/synthdefs`, starts `scsynth` with synthdef auto-load enabled, and prefers a real JACK/Scarlett graph before falling back to `pw-jack`; `restart_composer.sh` now restarts the composer gracefully and verifies the new PID instead of rebuilding synthdefs with `/d_recv`; and `cypherclaw_boot.sh` no longer blindly sends `/n_set` to master node `99999` after boot.
CHANGELOG.md:915:- Relaxed composer restart verification to the real steady-state condition: `restart_composer.sh` now waits for any healthy `duet_composer.py` process instead of only trusting the very first child PID, which avoids false failures during the current live startup race.
CHANGELOG.md:916:- Made the composer restart truly session-detached: `restart_composer.sh` now launches `duet_composer.py` with `nohup setsid ... </dev/null` so the live composer survives operator SSH/session teardown instead of disappearing with the parent shell.
CHANGELOG.md:917:- Added a persistent cold-boot path for the live AV runtime: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now restarts `start_audio.sh`, `restart_composer.sh`, `self_listener.py`, `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` under detached sessions, and `cypherclaw-av-stack.service` can bind that stack to `graphical.target` so music and the face monitor return after reboot without a manual SSH recovery.
CHANGELOG.md:919:- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
CHANGELOG.md:940:- Wired stable EMSD sample capture into the live runtime: added `capture_alias.py` plus `sample_dsp_activity.py`, taught `room_listener.py`, `contact_listener.py`, `theramini_listener.py`, and `self_listener.py` to mirror fresh clips into `/tmp/room_capture.wav`, `/tmp/contact_capture.wav`, `/tmp/theramini_capture.wav`, and `/tmp/self_capture.wav`, and made `self_listener.py` publish `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` with concrete activity modes, trigger flags, and DSP/sample-control values derived from composer, cadence, and sensor state.
CHANGELOG.md:942:- Fed EMSD production plans into actual tracker playback: added `emsd_performance.py`, wired `duet_composer.py` to apply live mix/sample/DSP adjustments at the note boundary, extended `composer_emsd_extras()` with concrete sample capture metadata, and made the strongest top register fold down harder so notes above roughly `C6` are lowered an octave and the sharpest band is lowered two octaves.
CHANGELOG.md:943:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
CHANGELOG.md:945:- Folded the highest live octave down by one octave at playback time: `voice_shaping.py` now marks the extreme top band with a `pitch_multiplier`, and `play_voice()` applies that fold before sending OSC so CypherClaw's brightest instruments stop landing in the most painful register.
CHANGELOG.md:946:- Tightened title-hook coherence again: `hook_engine.py` now chooses title phrases from image-field-aware pools that also react to cadence, progression profile, hook type, and repertoire source titles, so CypherClaw can move between labels like `Low Light`, `Electric Circuits`, `Moving Lines`, and `Open Thresholds` without collapsing back to generic or repeated adjective-noun pairs.
CHANGELOG.md:947:- Very high-note playback shaping is now stronger and more explicit: `voice_shaping.py` emits best-effort `highpass_hz` and `saturation_mix` controls in addition to the existing top-octave gain/brightness/release shaping, and `play_voice()` forwards those controls so ear-splitting notes can be filtered and driven slightly when the live SynthDefs support it.
CHANGELOG.md:955:- Extended repertoire influence into tracker form memory: the live composer can now inherit a prior strong song's preferred progression profile, title/hook recall mode, form variant, and section-density bias before building the next tracker song.
CHANGELOG.md:956:- Made repertoire memory active instead of archival-only: `repertoire_memory.py` now returns forward-looking influence by family/cadence, `hook_engine.py` can answer or recall prior title/hook material, and the live composer can bias the next song's progression profile before score generation begins.
CHANGELOG.md:957:- Built the first complete M1-M6 musicianship package end to end: added `reharmonizer.py`, `hook_engine.py`, `arrangement_engine.py`, `ear_engine.py`, `practice_curriculum.py`, `prosody_engine.py`, and `repertoire_memory.py`; extended `harmonic_planner.py`, `generative_scores.py`, `music_tracker.py`, `continuous_learner.py`, `duet_composer.py`, and `keyboard_chat.py` so tracker songs now carry section functions, cadence types, hook metadata, scene arrangement intent, practice-block focus, ear-metric evaluation, repertoire storage, and face-visible song titles/captions through the live runtime.
CHANGELOG.md:962:- Diversified family and harmonic planning across the day and week: `resolve_tracker_plan()` now rotates through day-phase and weekly-phase family palettes instead of pinning occupied daytime songs to one family, and it emits progression profiles like `open_day`, `lift`, `settling`, and `experiment` so the score generator changes chord motion as well as form.
CHANGELOG.md:963:- Added family-level motif memory to the live tracker path: `ContinuousLearner` now tags songs with tracker family, progression profile, cadence state, and patch context, `MelodicMemory` can retrieve matching fragments by keyword, and `score_from_mood()` now prefers and answers same-family/profile motifs instead of drawing only from a generic recent fragment pool.
CHANGELOG.md:965:- Gave the named house patches real musical identities instead of just voice pools: `score_from_mood()` is now patch-aware, so melody contour, bass/comping pattern, progression bank, dynamics, and register spread all change with the active house patch.
CHANGELOG.md:966:- Replaced the provisional tracker patch set with named house patches (`house_monastery`, `house_chamber`, `house_garden`, `house_procession`, `house_workshop`) and retired `bell` / `metal` from live runtime playback, so CypherClaw now stays inside a more coherent western-compatible ensemble even when the cast contains those older inharmonic voices.
CHANGELOG.md:968:- Replaced the inharmonic runtime `gong` playback voice with a tuned bowed substitute, so the live foundation voice sits inside western/modal harmonic material instead of fighting it.
CHANGELOG.md:972:- Widened tracker orchestration so CypherClaw can actually use the broader character-instrument registry: cast planning now keeps a support-role character in low-energy songs, tracker role hints recognize metal/grain/pad/tabla synths, and runtime voice routing preserves those explicit lane instruments instead of collapsing them to legacy fallbacks.
CHANGELOG.md:973:- Tuned tracker voice routing to be lane-aware again after the orchestration widening pass: ringing `metal`/`bell`/`pad` hints are normalized away from long quiet texture/counter lanes, and tracker runtime restores a pad safety fallback so subdued scenes do not sit on a constant unregulated tone.
CHANGELOG.md:974:- Added cadence-aware tracker voice softening for `wind_down` and sleep-adjacent scenes, so chirpy `pluck`/`kotekan`/`grain` cast hints are remapped toward bowed, breath, choir, or gong voices before late-night playback.
CHANGELOG.md:976:- Added explicit runtime voice aliases so unavailable or unsafe voices can degrade cleanly: `grain` now resolves to `breath`, and `tabla_ge` currently resolves to `tabla_tin` until a real `sw_tabla_ge` SynthDef is deployed.
CHANGELOG.md:983:- Made CypherClaw tracker solo cast-aware: the live composer now derives tracker lane voice hints from the active character cast and enforces a quiet foundation lane through subdued `Theme`/`Development`/`Recap` scenes.
CHANGELOG.md:1002:- Added a queue-backed Telegram `/monitor` built-in so live queue progress and active task status come from the authority DB instead of stale routed status text.
CHANGELOG.md:1003:- Unified queue-progress totals across Telegram and `sdp-cli`: counts now use live executable tasks and exclude only split parents.
