docs/20260402-cypherclaw-embodiment-prd.md:13:CypherClaw currently operates as a headless generative art system. It produces beautiful work, but it has no presence. A visitor encounters monitors displaying art but has no sense of meeting *something*. There is no face, no voice, no way to speak back. The system generates but does not converse. It observes but does not acknowledge.
docs/20260402-cypherclaw-embodiment-prd.md:92:When N ≥ 2 voices confirm the same event type within a configurable time window:
docs/20260402-cypherclaw-embodiment-prd.md:100:- **Sensor disconnected:** Graceful removal. No crash. Remaining voices redistribute visual weight. Log the event in The Archive.
docs/20260402-cypherclaw-embodiment-prd.md:117:- **Content:** Full GlyphWeave output shaped by all sensory voices. The broader emotional landscape. When the user types, the gallery responds to the semantic and rhythmic content of their input, but text itself appears on the face.
