my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:11:1. **Memory of place.** A continuous rolling buffer of contact + room input. When something is acoustically interesting (a transient cluster, a novel spectral signature, a sustained drone the room produces on its own), the buffer is captured to disk, tagged with the arc phase / mood / time / who-is-in-room, and made available to future scenes. Days later, those moments return — never literally, always granularly transformed — as quiet textures. The room composes itself through CypherClaw.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:13:2. **Self-quotation.** When the composer plays a phrase that scored high on arc payoff, low on click count, and matched intended mood, that phrase is sampled back from `SuperCollider:out_1` and stored under `samples/self/`. Next session, transformed fragments of that phrase return as melodic memory — the Eno tape-loop / Reich phasing aesthetic. The music remembers itself.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:22:4. **Self-listening as composition.** The composer's own past output is a primary source. CypherClaw learns from itself.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:48:**Phase 4 — Composer integration (CCS-022..CCS-028).** Mode-driven sampler density (solitary heavy, working light, etc.); `select_sample()` wired into cast/instrument-patch path so the composer treats the sampler as a first-class voice; self-quotation loop captures composer output when arc-payoff is high; keyboard/Theramini capture during human play; per-mode effects-bus presets; operator diagnostics surface currently-active samples. End of phase: pieces start to noticeably *cite themselves* across sessions, and the room's acoustic history becomes audible material.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:50:**Phase 5 — Verification + observability (CCS-029..CCS-033).** Per-piece sampler-event metrics; anti-pattern detection for sampler dominating (over-quote) or never appearing (silent quintet member); a sample-usage journal that records which samples played in which pieces with what transformations; end-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw confirming the daemon is capturing, the selector is choosing, the synth is playing, and the self-listener is observing the right output peaks. End of phase: composer can demonstrate a piece that uses 1 self-quotation + 1 room-capture + 1 library sample, all selector-chosen, all routed through the effects bus, all surfaced in the diagnostics dashboard.
