my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:89:| CCS-001 | Define `SampleRecord` dataclass with sample-id, path, source, character tags, pitch, duration, captured-at, arc context, RMS, peak, transient density. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_library.SampleRecord` defined with fields: `sample_id` (UUID), `path` (Path), `source` (Literal['library','self','room','contact','theramini','keyboard']), `character_tags` (frozenset[str]), `pitch_hz` (float \| None), `pitch_confidence` (float), `duration_sec` (float), `captured_at` (datetime), `arc_phase` (str \| None), `mood` (dict[str,float] \| None), `presence` (Literal['present','none','unknown'] \| None), `rms` (float), `peak` (float), `transient_density` (float), `gain_db` (float, default 0.0)<br/>- dataclass is frozen and JSON-serializable; ISO-8601 timestamp round-trip<br/>- tests verify schema, defaults, JSON round-trip, and rejection of out-of-range values |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:101:| CCS-013 | Per-voice gate-controlled lifecycle: composer can `play_sampler(record, duration_sec)` for fire-and-forget OR `start_sampler(record) -> handle; stop_sampler(handle)` for sustained voices. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch.play_sampler(record, duration_sec, **params)` schedules a fire-and-forget grain cloud with an internal envelope of `duration_sec`<br/>- `start_sampler` / `stop_sampler` returns/uses a handle for sustained sampler voices that match the bowed/pad lifecycle<br/>- both code paths feed through the same `dispatch_sample` core<br/>- tests verify both lifecycles and that they can run concurrently without buffer-id collision |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:105:| CCS-017 | Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → "warm"; narrow-band high-centroid → "metallic"; sustained_amplitude_ratio>0.7 → "sustained"; transient_density>3/sec → "percussive"; pitch_confidence>0.7 → "harmonic"; etc.<br/>- tests verify each heuristic against canned fixtures and that the merged record validates against `SampleRecord` schema |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:107:| CCS-019 | Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` post-song hook calls `sample_capture_daemon::self_quote(score_summary)` when arc_payoff > 0.6 AND click_count == 0 AND mode != working_ambience<br/>- daemon captures from `SuperCollider:out_1` (via `system:capture_X` after a small JACK loopback connection it manages itself) the 4-second window centered on the moment of peak rolling_peak during the song<br/>- saves to `samples/self/` with `arc_phase`, `mood`, `mode`, and a `self_quote_source_song_id` extra tag<br/>- tests with a mock self-listener stream and arc-payoff fixture verify trigger condition, capture window, and tag propagation |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:111:| CCS-023 | Per-mode sampler density gates: composer plays `floor(sampler_density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(sampler_density)` sampler events per piece (clamped 0..total). | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` reads `mode_sampler_density` and schedules sampler events accordingly within the song's tracker timeline<br/>- evening_reflection at 0.65 produces noticeably more sampler events than working_ambience at 0.10 in 100-piece simulated runs<br/>- never schedules more sampler events than total phrases in the piece<br/>- tests verify density-to-count math, clamp behavior, and per-mode separation |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:115:| CCS-027 | Surface "currently sampling X" + "playing sample Y from source Z" in `operator_diagnostics.py` and the face/inkplate display. | MUST | T2 | - `operator_diagnostics.py::sampler_status() -> dict` returns `{capture_active: bool, capture_seconds_buffered: int, last_capture: dict, current_playback: list[dict]}`<br/>- daemon writes `/tmp/sampler_state.json` every 1 sec for the diagnostic to read<br/>- face/inkplate renderers gain a one-line "♫ sampling room" / "♫ memory: <self/2026-04-25>" banner<br/>- tests verify state-file schema and diagnostic output format |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:116:| CCS-028 | Composer post-piece hook: write a sample-usage journal entry per piece (which samples played, what transformations, what arc payoff). | MUST | T1 | - `samples/usage_journal.jsonl` appended one line per piece with `piece_id`, `started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used: list[{sample_id, source, transposition, fx_preset, played_at_row}]`, `arc_payoff`, `clicks`<br/>- journal is durable (fsynced after each line)<br/>- tests verify schema and atomicity |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:119:| CCS-031 | End-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw: capture a known room sound, watch the composer self-quote it within 3 pieces, verify the self-listener observes the resulting peaks. | MUST | T1 | - `my-claw/tests/test_sampler_e2e.py` (skipped on CI, runs on cypherclaw via `pytest -m cypherclaw_e2e`)<br/>- plays a 4-second sine sweep through the speakers, lets contact/room mic capture it, waits for the daemon to detect+tag, forces the composer to compose 3 short pieces, asserts at least one of them dispatched a sampler with the captured sample<br/>- self-listener observes nonzero peak in the expected scene<br/>- documented in `docs/sampler-smoke-test.md` |
